Executive Profile
Emily K. Rafferty  Director, PJT Partners Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships70$125,000
Background

		Ms. Emily K. Rafferty serves as the President of Metropolitan Museum of Art. Ms. Rafferty serves as the Chief Administrative Officer of Metropolitan, where she is responsible for supervising more than 2,500 museum employees in the areas of finance, technology and information services, legal affairs, development, membership, communications, construction and facilities management, merchandising, government relations, human resources and security. She serves as an Ex Officio ... Member at the Museum’s Board. She has been on the staff of the Metropolitan Museum since 1976. She began her career at the Met as an administrator for Corporate, Foundation and Individual Fundraising and then served as manager of Development from 1981 to 1984. From 1984 to 1996, She served as vice president for Development and Membership. She served as Senior Vice President of Development and Membership in 1996 and then to senior vice president for External Affairs in 1999. In this position, she was responsible for the strategic planning for and implementation of all of the institution’s fundraising activities, along with special events, admissions and visitor services. She also led the effort to create the Metropolitan’s website and to create and implement its multicultural audience and membership initiative. She began her professional career in 1971 as an assistant to David Rockefeller, Jr., in Boston. From 1973 to 1975 she served as Deputy Director of education at Boston's Institute of Contemporary Art. She served as the Chairman of the Board at The Federal Reserve Bank of New York from January 1, 2013 to January 16, 2017 and has been its Director since 2011. She serves as the Chairperson of NYC & Company, Inc. She has been a Director of PJT Partners Inc. since October 1, 2015. She serves as a Director of National September 11 Memorial & Museum at the World Trade Center Foundation, Inc. Ms. Rafferty received her bachelor's degree from Boston University. She holds Honorary Doctorate in law from Fairfield University and Doctorate from College Of New Rochelle, The (Inc).Read Full Background




